UML:TaggedValue.value: User services provide the visual interface for presenting information and gathering data. They also secure the business services needed to deliver the required business capabilities and integrate the user with the applications to perform a business process.
Actual object will be passed by the Edit operation
Main program in the ordersys example

Business services are the bridge between user and data services. They respond to requests from the user (or other business services) in order to execute a business task. They accomplish this by applying formal procedures and business rules to the relevant data. When the needed data resides on a database server , they secure the data services needed to accomplish the business task or apply the business rule. This protocol insulates the user from direct interaction with the database. Because business rules tend to change more frequently than the specific business tasks they support, they are ideal candidates for encapsulating in components that are physically separate from the application logic itself.

Data services maintain, access, and update data. They also manage and satisfy requests to manipulate data that are initiated by business services. Separating data services allows the data structure and access mechanisms to be maintained, modified, or, if necessary, even re-architected without affecting business or user services.

The use case starts when the Order Administrator has requested the system to display all orders. The system then shows a list of the current registered orders. The actor can at any time select (or deselect) orders displayed in the list and do the following: - Create a new order. - Remove an order. - Update the information about an order.
Create a new order ------------------------------ The actor has requested the system to create a new order. The system assigns a unique order identity to the new order and presents the following information: - Order identity - Customer (default) - Order rows (empty) - Total sum (=0)
The system requests the actor to enter the following information about the new order: - Customer - For each order row: - Article type - Quantity
At any time the actor can create (see Create Order Row), remove (see Remove Order Row) or update (see Update Order Row) an entered order row or change customer. When the ordered quantity of an order row is updated and saved, the new order sum is displayed.
The actor can choose to save the information or cancel the operation. If the actor decides to save the information, the new order is created, the information is saved, and the displayed list of orders is updated. If the actor decides to cancel the operation, any created order rows are deleted and the backlog of the corresponding article types are updated.
Remove an order --------------------------- The actor has requested the system to remove one or several selected orders. The actor is prompted to accept or cancel the operation. If the actor accepts the operation, the system removes the order(s) from the system, updates the article backlogs, and updates the displayed list of registered orders.
Update the information about an order ------------------------------------------------------------ The actor has requested the system to change the registered information about an order. The system presents the following information about the selected order: - Order identity - Customer - For each order row: - Article type - Ordered quantity
At any time the actor can remove (see Remove Order Row) or update (see Update Order Row) an entered order row or change customer. When the ordered quantity of an order row is updated, the new order sum is displayed.
The actor can choose to save the information or cancel the operation. If the actor decides to save, the changed information is saved. If the actor decides to cancel the operation, any created order rows are deleted and the backlog of the corresponding article types are updated.
Create Order Row ----------------------------- The actor can choose to save the information or cancel the operation. If the actor decides to save the information, the new order row is created, the ordered quantity is saved, the backlog of the selected article type is increased, and the displayed list of order rows is updated.
Remove Order Row -------------------------------- The system deletes the selected Order Row and updates the backlog of the corresponding article type accordingly.
Update Order Row ------------------------------ The actor can choose to save the information or cancel the operation. If the actor decides to save the information, the new quantity is saved, the backlog of the selected article type is updated accordingly.

The use case starts when the Order Administrator has requested the system to display all customers. The system then shows a list of all customers in the customer register. The actor can at any time select (or deselect) customers displayed in the list and do the following: - Add a customer. - Remove a customer. - Update the information about a customer.
Add a customer ------------------------- The actor has requested the system to add a customer to the customer register. The system presents the following information and requests the actor to change any of the information: - Identity - Name - Address The actor can choose to save the information or cancel the operation. If the actor decides to save the information, the new customer is created in the register, the information is saved, and the displayed list of customers is updated.
Remove customer ----------------------------- The actor has requested the system to remove one or several selected customers. The actor is prompted to accept or cancel the operation. If the actor accepts the operation, the system removes the customer(s) from the register and updates the displayed list of registered customers.
Update the information about a customer ---------------------------------------------------------------- The actor has requested the system to edit the registered information about a customer. The system presents the information and allows the actor to change any of the following information: - Identity - Name - Address The actor is prompted to accept or cancel the operation. If the actor accepts the operation, the system saves the changed information and updates the displayed list of registered customers.

The use case starts when the Store Administrator has requested the system to display all orders. The system then shows a list of the orders. The actor can select to do any of the following: - Print an order. - Execute an order.
Print an order --------------------- The actor has requested the system to print the selected order. The system requests printer information from the user. If the actor decides to print, all information about the order is printed as requested.
Exectute an order ---------------------------- The actor has requested the system to execute a selected order. For each order row of the selected order, the actor is requested to confirm that the ordered quantity has been delivered or define the remaining quantity to deliver later.
For each order row, the system reduces the quantity and backlog of the corresponding article type according to the actors instructions. If the ordered quantity was confirmed, the system deletes the corresponding order row.
When the actor is finished the system prints a delivery note listing the amount and price for each delivered article type, and the total sum. If the ordered quantity was confirmed for all order rows, the order is deleted.

The use case starts when the Store Administrator has requested the system to display all types of articles. The system then shows a list of all article types in the store. The actor can at any time select (or deselect) article types displayed in the list and do the following: - Add an article type. - Remove an article type. - Update the information about an article type.
Add an article type ----------------------------- The actor has requested the system to add a new article type to the store. The system presents the following information and requests the actor to change any of the information: - Identity - Name - Quantity - Price - Delivery time - Description The actor can choose to save the information or cancel the operation. If the actor decides to save the information, the new article type is created in the register, the information is saved, and the displayed list of article types is updated.
Remove article types --------------------------------- The actor has requested the system to remove one or several selected article types. The actor is prompted to accept or cancel the operation. If the actor accepts the operation, the system removes the article type(s) from the set of available article types and updates the displayed list of article types.
Update the information about an article type --------------------------------------------------------------------- The actor has requested the system to edit the registered information about an article type. The system presents the information and allows the actor to change any of the following information: - Identity - Name - Quantity - Backlog - Price - Delivery time - Description The actor is prompted to accept or cancel the operation. If the actor accepts the operation, the system saves the changed information and updates the displayed list of available article types.

This actor represents a person who is responsible for the store of articles and for executing the registered orders.
